}}\n'''Thom S. Rainer''' (born July 16, 1955) is an [[United States|American]] writer, researcher, speaker, and former president and CEO of [[LifeWay Christian Resources]], an entity of the [[Southern Baptist Convention]]<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.sbc.net/aboutus/entities/lifeway.asp |publisher=Southern Baptist Convention |title=LifeWay Christian Resources |accessdate=2017-01-23}}</ref> in [[Nashville, Tennessee]]. He is the author of several best selling books, including ''I Am a Church Member'', named a [[CBA (Christian trade association)|CBA]] #1 Best Seller (2013\u20132014) and Monthly Best Seller (2013\u20132015).<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.christianretailing.com/index.php/newsletter/latest/26466-i-am-a-church-member-becomes-no-1-cba-best-seller |title='I Am a Church Member' becomes No. 1 CBA best-seller |publisher= Christian Retailing |date= |accessdate=2017-01-20}}</ref> It was also recognized as a Monthly Best Seller (2013\u20132015), a Gold Medallion Award winner (2015),<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ecpa.org/news/230065/ECPA-Presents-Diamond-Awards-to-three-Non-Fiction-titles-for-over-10-million-in-sales-17-other-titl.htm |title=ECPA Presents Diamond Awards to three Non-Fiction titles for over 10 million in sales; 17 other titles |publisher=ECPA |date= |accessdate=2017-01-20}}</ref> and a Platinum Book Award winner (2016)<ref>{{cite web|url=http://christianbookexpo.com/salesawards/ |title=Gold / Platinum / Diamond Book Awards Winners |publisher=Christian Book Expo |date= |accessdate=2017-01-20}}</ref> by the [[Evangelical Christian Publishers Association]], and recognized by Leadership Journal as Best of the Best in the Leaders Outer Life category (2013);<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.bhpublishinggroup.com/press-release/i-am-a-church-member-by-thom-rainer-impacts-1-million-people-in-its-first-two-years-of-release |title=I AM A CHURCH MEMBER BY THOM RAINER IMPACTS 1 MILLION PEOPLE IN ITS FIRST TWO YEARS OF RELEASE |publisher=B&H Publishing Group |date= |accessdate=2017-01-20}}</ref> ''Autopsy of a Deceased Church'', Christian Retailing's Best Book of the Year: Church and Culture (2015);<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.frontgatemedia.com/winners-announced-in-2015-christian-retailings-best-awards/ |title=Winners announced in 2015 Christian Retailing's Best awards |publisher=Front Gate Media |date=2015-07-06 |accessdate=2017-01-20}}</ref> and ''Simple Church'', the 2007 ''[[Christianity Today]]'' Book Award winner in the Church/Pastoral Leadership category.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.christianitytoday.com/ct/2007/june/8.36.html |title=2007 Christianity Today Book Awards |publisher=Christianity Today |date= |accessdate=2013-09-06}}</ref>\n\n==Biography==\nRainer was born in [[Union Springs, Alabama]] and is a 1977 graduate of the [[University of Alabama]], majoring in corporate finance with minors in [[statistics]] and [[economics]]. He began his career as a cash management officer (1977\u201380) at Trust Company of Georgia, now [[SunTrust]]. By age 25, Rainer became a fifth-generation banker and the youngest vice president<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.churchcentral.com/blog/Learn-the-Secret-of-Loving-Your-Work |title=Learn the Secret of Loving Your Work |publisher=ChurchCentral.com |date=2010-10-17 |accessdate=2013-09-06 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20101028180429/http://www.churchcentral.com/blog/Learn-the-Secret-of-Loving-Your-Work |archivedate=2010-10-28 }}</ref> for corporate lending of [[SouthTrust Bank]] in [[Anniston, Alabama]] (1980\u201383).\n\nRainer entered Christian vocational ministry in 1982 and earned his [[Master of Divinity]] and [[Doctor of Philosophy]] degrees from the [[Southern Baptist Theological Seminary]] in [[Louisville, Kentucky]]. He served as pastor of churches in Alabama, Florida, Kentucky and Indiana prior to joining the faculty of SBTS in 1994 as founding dean of the [[Billy Graham School of Missions, Evangelism and Church Growth]].<ref>[http://www.sbts.edu/bgs/faculty/thom-rainer/ ] {{webarchive |url=https://web.archive.org/web/20100527113648/http://www.sbts.edu/bgs/faculty/thom-rainer/ |date=May 27, 2010 }}</ref> Also while serving at SBTS, Rainer founded and served as president and CEO of the [[Rainer Group]].\n\nIn September 2005, Rainer was unanimously elected by the trustees of LifeWay Christian Resources to succeed [[James T. Draper]] as the ninth president of LifeWay,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.bpnews.net/bpnews.asp?id=21609 |title=Baptist Press -Thom Rainer gets unanimous vote as LifeWay president-elect - News with a Christian Perspective |publisher=Bpnews.net |accessdate=2013-09-06 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120403011143/http://www.bpnews.net/bpnews.asp?id=21609 |archivedate=2012-04-03 }}</ref> one of the world's largest Christian resource providers.<ref>{{cite book|url=https://books.google.com/?id=-fYDGf4U1psC&pg=PT774&lpg=PT774&dq=lifeway+world%27s+largest+christian+publisher#v=onepage&q=lifeway%20world's%20largest%20christian%20publisher&f=false |author1-last=Pope |author1-first=Alice |title=2010 Novel & Short Story Writer's Market |date=2010 |accessdate=2017-01-23|isbn=9781599635675 }}</ref> Shortly after assuming the presidency, Rainer established B&H Academic,<ref>{{cite web |url=https://blogs.thegospelcoalition.org/trevinwax/2013/12/13/know-your-southern-baptists-thom-rainer-2/ |title=KNOW YOUR SOUTHERN BAPTISTS: THOM RAINER |publisher=Kingdom People |date=2013-12-13 |accessdate=2017-01-23 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170202022926/https://blogs.thegospelcoalition.org/trevinwax/2013/12/13/know-your-southern-baptists-thom-rainer-2/ |archive-date=2017-02-02 |url-status=dead }}</ref> a branch of LifeWay's [[B&H Publishing Group]], to provide pastors, seminary professors and students with theologically conservative commentaries, academic monographs and other biblically-based resources.\n\n==Blog and podcast==\nRainer blogs at ThomRainer.com and hosts the highly rated Rainer on Leadership Podcast.<ref>[https://itunes.apple.com/us/podcast/rainer-on-leadership/id638894745?mt=2/ Rainer on Leadership]</ref> Rainer on Leadership, a twice weekly podcast which experienced 265 percent growth between 2014 and 2016, was started as a companion to Rainer's blog. It surpassed 100,000 monthly downloads in September 2016.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.bpnews.net/47740 |title=SBC DIGEST: Surgeon Rebekah Naylor honored; Rainer podcast surpasses 1M; Digby to lead MBC ethics arm; New FCA leader named |date=2016-10-18 |accessdate=2017-01-20}}</ref> His blog is listed at #6 on Redeeming God's list of Christian blogs.<ref>[https://redeeminggod.com/100-top-christian-blogs/ The 100 Top Christian Blogs]</ref>\n\n==LifeWay Research==\nNot long after becoming president of LifeWay, Rainer announced the formation of [[LifeWay Research]] for the purpose of assisting and equipping church leaders with insight and advice that will lead to greater levels of church health and effectiveness.<ref>[http://baptistpress.net/bpnews.asp?id=23234 ] {{webarchive |url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110723022927/http://baptistpress.net/bpnews.asp?id=23234 |date=July 23, 2011 }}</ref>\n\nLifeWay Research is frequently cited in religious and mainstream media, including [[The New York Times]],<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2016/10/17/us/donald-trump-evangelicals-republican-vote.html |title=Donald Trump Reveals Evangelical Rifts That Could Shape Politics for Years |work=New York Times |date=2016-10-17 |accessdate=2017-01-20}}</ref> [[USA Today]],<ref>{{cite web |url=http://content.usatoday.com/topics/topic/Religion+and+beliefs/Surveys/LifeWay+Research |archive-url=https://wayback.archive-it.org/all/20110915174345/http://content.usatoday.com/topics/topic/Religion+and+beliefs/Surveys/LifeWay+Research |url-status=dead |archive-date=2011-09-15 |title=LifeWay Research Topics Page - USATODAY.com |publisher=Content.usatoday.com |accessdate=2013-09-06 }}</ref> [[Washington Post]],<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/pb/news/acts-of-faith/wp/2016/10/07/donald-trumps-pastor-problem-40-percent-of-protestant-pastors-are-still-undecided/?outputType=accessibility&nid=menu_nav_accessibilityforscreenreader |title=Donald Trump's pastor problem: 40 percent of Protestant ministers are still undecided |publisher=Washington Post |date=2016-10-07 |accessdate=2017-01-20}}</ref> [[Christianity Today]],<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.christianitytoday.com/edstetzer/2016/november/lifeway-research-friends-and-family-matter-more-than-money.html |title=LifeWay Research: Friends and Family Matter More Than Money When It Comes to Giving Thanks |publisher=Christianity Today |date=2016-11-24 |accessdate=2017-01-20}}</ref> [[The Christian Post]],<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.christianpost.com/author/lifeway-research/ |title=Survey: Pastors Say Identifying With Denomination Will Become Less Vital |publisher=Christianpost.com |accessdate=25 February 2015}}</ref> and [[Baptist Press]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.bpnews.net/bpnews.asp?id=34409 |title=Baptist Press -BP 2010: YEAR IN REVIEW - LifeWay Research: Recession catches up to U.S. churches - News with a Christian Perspective |publisher=Bpnews.net |accessdate=2013-09-06 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120403011216/http://www.bpnews.net/bpnews.asp?id=34409 |archivedate=2012-04-03 }}</ref>\n\n==Great Commission resurgence==\nIn the 2005 Spring edition of the ''[[Southern Baptist Journal of Theology]]'', Rainer published a tribute and a review of the [[Southern Baptist Convention conservative resurgence]] after 25 years. The article entitled \"A Resurgence Not Yet Realized,\" noted that, though a theological turnaround had taken place in the Southern Baptist Convention, there was little indication that a resurgence of evangelism had taken place in the churches. In the article Rainer called for a \"great commission resurgence\", a phrase that would become the nomenclature for a renewed Great Commission emphasis in the SBC years later.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.pray4gcr.com/2010/05/thom-rainer-president-of-lifeway-doing-nothing-is-not-an-option-calls-for-gcr/ |accessdate=February 2, 2011 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110715111724/http://www.pray4gcr.com/2010/05/thom-rainer-president-of-lifeway-doing-nothing-is-not-an-option-calls-for-gcr/ |archivedate=July 15, 2011 }}</ref>\n\n==Awards and recognition==\nIn the spring of 2004, Rainer was invited to be a member of the Society of Fellows for the R. G. Lee Center for Christian Ministry at [[Union University]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.uu.edu/centers/rglee/fellows.cfm |title=Society of Fellows |publisher=Union University |accessdate=2017-01-23}}</ref>\n\nIn 2008, Rainer received the M. E. Dodd Denominational Service Award from Union University.<ref name=\"uu.edu\">{{cite web|url=http://www.uu.edu/news/release.cfm?ID=1360 |title=Union presents Dodd Award to Rainer - News Release &#124; Union University |publisher=Uu.edu |date=2008-06-13 |accessdate=2013-09-06}}</ref> The Dodd Award is the highest denominational service award Union gives. It is named for the man who was a Union alumnus, served as president of the Southern Baptist Convention and who was the father of today's [[Cooperative Program]],<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.cpmissions.net/2003/what%20is%20cp.asp |title=Cooperative Program (CP) Missions |publisher=Cpmissions.net |date= |accessdate=2013-09-06}}</ref> the method by which Southern Baptists pool their resources to fund their mission efforts. The award is given annually to a leader within the SBC who displays excellence and leadership in Southern Baptist life, as well as friendship and commitment to Union University. Past recipients include Jimmy Draper (2004), [[Adrian Rogers]] (2005), [[Morris Chapman]] (2006) and [[Frank Page (Southern Baptist)|Frank Page]] (2007).\n\nOn November 11, 2010, Rainer received the Donald A. McGavran award for outstanding leadership in church growth from the Great Commission Research Network.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://townhall.com/news/religion/2010/11/17/sbc_digest_rainer_receives_mcgavran_church_growth_award;_wright_speaks_at_southwestern;_ |title=SBC DIGEST: Rainer receives McGavran church growth award; Wright speaks at Southwestern;&nbsp;... - Baptist Press - Breaking News \u2013 Latest World, US, Science, Entertainment, Election, Technology News and Current Events |publisher=Townhall.com |date=2010-11-17 |accessdate=2013-09-06}}</ref> According to the GCRN president Bob Whitesel, Rainer's \"research and writings have been and continue to be key resources to those who care about church health and growth.\"<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.lifeway.com/article/170559/ |archive-url=https://archive.is/20130128122317/http://www.lifeway.com/article/170559/ |url-status=dead |archive-date=2013-01-28 |title=Thom Rainer named 2010 Donald A. McGavran award recipient |publisher=Lifeway.com |date=2010-11-16 |accessdate=2013-09-06 }}</ref>\n\nIn 2010, Rainer was inducted into the Carl F. H. Henry Society of Fellows at Union University and provided Union's graduation keynote address.<ref name=\"uu.edu\"/> Rainer was also appointed to serve as a trustee board member for Union by action of the Tennessee Baptist Convention.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.tnbaptist.org/page.asp?cat=aboutus&subcat=boards |title=Tennessee Baptist Convention |publisher=Tnbaptist.org |accessdate=2013-09-06 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131005072140/http://www.tnbaptist.org/page.asp?cat=aboutus&subcat=boards |archivedate=2013-10-05 }}</ref>\n\nThe Southern Baptist Theological Seminary awarded Rainer its Alumnus of the Year award in 2013<ref>{{cite web|url=http://news.sbts.edu/2013/06/13/at-2013-alumni-luncheon-southern-seminary-names-thom-rainer-alumnus-of-the-year/ |title=At 2013 alumni luncheon, Southern Seminary names Thom Rainer alumnus of the year |publisher=Southern News |date=2013-06-13 |accessdate=2017-01-20}}</ref> and the E.Y. Mullins Distinguished Denominational Service Award in 2014. In presenting the award, Southern's president, [[Albert Mohler]], recognized Rainer \"for his 'remarkable legacy of leadership' as pastor, scholar, teacher, and founding dean of the Billy Graham School, as well as for his role as author, speaker, and president of LifeWay Christian Resources of the Southern Baptist Convention.\"<ref>{{cite web|url=http://news.sbts.edu/2014/10/15/southern-seminary-trustees-celebrate-20th-anniversary-of-billy-graham-school/ |title=Southern Seminary trustees celebrate 20th anniversary of Billy Graham School |publisher=Southern News |date=2014-10-15 |accessdate=2017-01-20}}</ref>\n\n==Speaking and teaching==\nExamples of his speaking and teaching engagements include:\n*\"Evangelism and Church Growth in the Southern Baptist Convention,\" Baptist Identity II Conference<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.uu.edu/events/baptistidentity/ |title=Baptist Identity II: Convention, Cooperation and Controversy - Feb. 15-17, 2007 |publisher=Uu.edu |date= |accessdate=2013-09-06}}</ref>\n*\"The Church and Contemporary Culture,\" University of the Cumberlands.<ref>[http://gradweb.ucumberlands.edu/religion/macs/profiles/guest-speakers ] {{webarchive |url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110720082314/http://gradweb.ucumberlands.edu/religion/macs/profiles/guest-speakers |date=July 20, 2011 }}</ref>\n*Christian Executive Officers (CEO) Fellowship<ref>[http://www.ceofellowship.com/thom-rainer.html ]{{dead link|date=September 2013}}</ref>\n*The Commission on Evangelism<ref>{{cite web|url=http://nccumcevangelism.org/acw-advance-academy/ |accessdate=February 2, 2011 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20101023162744/http://nccumcevangelism.org/acw-advance-academy/ |archivedate=October 23, 2010 }}</ref>\n\n\nRainer holds the title of Distinguished Professor of Evangelism and Church Growth (2006) at The Southern Baptist Theological Seminary, and also lectures at [[Southeastern Baptist Theological Seminary]].\n\n==Works==\nRainer has written or co-written 27 books and more than 200 articles. His books and a selection of his articles include:\n\n===Books===\n*{{cite book |editor1-last=Rainer |editor1-first=Thom S. |title=Evangelism in the Twenty-First Century: the critical issues - Twenty-one contributors writing in honor of Lewis A. Drummond |location=Wheaton, IL |publisher=[[Harold Shaw Publisher]] |date=1989 |isbn=978-0-877-88238-1 |oclc=19514886 }}\n*{{cite book |author1-last=Rainer |author1-first=Thom S. |author1-mask=3 |title=The Book of Church Growth: history, theology, and principles |location=Nashville, TN |publisher=[[B&H Publishing Group|Broadman Press]] |date=1993 |isbn=978-0-805-41157-7 |oclc=26589881 }}\n*{{cite book |author1-last=Rainer |author1-first=Thom S. |author1-mask=3 |title=Eating the Elephant: bite-sized steps to achieve long-term growth in your church |location=Nashville, TN |publisher=B&H Publishing Group |date=1994 |isbn=978-0-805-46140-4 |oclc=29703199 |edition=1st |url=https://archive.org/details/eatingelephantbi0000rain }}\n*{{cite book |author1-last=Rainer |author1-first=Thom S. |author1-mask=3 |title=Giant Awakenings: making the most of 9 surprising trends that can benefit your church |location=Nashville, TN |publisher=B&H Publishing Group |date=1995 |isbn=978-0-805-46173-2 |oclc=31412089 }}\n*{{cite book |author1-last=Rainer |author1-first=Thom S. |author1-mask=3 |author2-last=Silva |author2-first=Michael |title=Experiencing Revival: A Guide to Personal Renewal and Evangelistic Revival in Your Church |location=La Mirada, CA |publisher=[[Church Growth Institute]] |date=1996 |isbn=978-1-570-52058-7 }}\n*{{cite book |editor1-last=Rainer |editor1-first=Thom S. |editor1-mask=3 |editor2-last=Drummond |editor2-first=Lewis |title=Biblical Affirmations for Evangelism |location=Minneapolis, MN |publisher=World Wide Publications |date=1996 |isbn=0-89066-284-3 }}\n*{{cite book |author1-last=Rainer |author1-first=Thom S. |author1-mask=3 |title=Effective Evangelistic Churches: successful churches reveal what works, and what doesn't |location=Nashville, TN |publisher=B&H Publishing Group |date=1996 |isbn=978-0-805-45402-4 |oclc=34410663 }}\n*{{cite book |author1-last=Rainer |author1-first=Thom S. |author1-mask=3 |title=The Bridger Generation: America's second largest generation, what they believe, how to reach them |location=Nashville, TN |publisher=B&H Publishing Group |date=1997 |isbn=978-0-805-46296-8 |oclc=36746379 |url-access=registration |url=https://archive.org/details/bridgergeneratio0000rain }}\n*{{cite book |author1-last=Rainer |author1-first=Thom S. |author1-mask=3 |author2-last=Wagner |author2-first=C. Peter |author2-link=C. Peter Wagner |author3-last=Towns |author3-first=Elmer L. |author3-link=Elmer L. Towns |title=The Every Church Guide to Growth: how any plateaued church can grow |location=Nashville, TN |publisher=B&H Publishing Group |date=1998 |isbn=978-0-805-40192-9 |oclc=38747534 }}\n*{{cite book |author1-last=Rainer |author1-first=Thom S. |author1-mask=3 |title=High expectations : the remarkable secret for keeping people in your church |location=Nashville, TN |publisher=B&H Publishing Group |date=1999 |isbn=978-0-805-41266-6 |oclc=39335543 }}\n*{{cite book |author1-last=Rainer |author1-first=Thom S. |author1-mask=3 |title=Surprising Insights from the Unchurched |location=Grand Rapids, MI |publisher=Zondervan |date=2001 |isbn=978-0-310-23648-1 |oclc=46678185 |url=https://archive.org/details/surprisinginsigh00thom }}\n*{{cite book |author1-last=Rainer |author1-first=Thom S. |author1-mask=3 |title=The Unchurched Next Door: understanding faith stages as keys to sharing your faith |location=Grand Rapids, MI |publisher=Zondervan |date=2003 |isbn=978-0-310-24860-6 |oclc=52203016 }}\n*{{cite book |author1-last=Rainer |author1-first=Thom S. |author1-mask=3 |author2-last=Lawless |author2-first=Charles E. |title=Eating the Elephant: Leading the Established Church to Growth |location=Syracuse, NY |publisher=[[Pinnacle Publishers]] |date=2003 |isbn=978-0-974-23060-3 |edition=Revised and expanded }} - updated version of the 1994 title\n*{{cite book |author1-last=Rainer |author1-first=Thom S. |author1-mask=3 |title=Breakout Churches: discover how to make the leap |location=Grand Rapids, MI |publisher=Zondervan |date=2005 |isbn=978-0-310-25745-5 |oclc=54988771 |url=https://archive.org/details/breakoutchurches00thom_0 }}\n*{{cite book |editor1-last=Rainer |editor1-first=Thom S. |editor1-mask=3 |editor2-last=Lawless |editor2-first=Charles E. |title=The Challenge of the Great Commission |location=Syracuse, NY |publisher=Pinnacle Publishers |date=2005 |isbn=978-0-974-23061-0 |oclc= }}\n*{{cite book |author1-last=Rainer |author1-first=Thom S. |author1-mask=3 |title=The Unexpected Journey: conversations with people who turned from other beliefs to Jesus |location=Grand Rapids, MI |publisher=Zondervan |date=2005 |isbn=978-0-310-25741-7 |oclc=60491957 }}\n*{{cite book |author1-last=Rainer |author1-first=Thom S. |author1-mask=3 |author2-last=Geiger |author2-first=Eric |title=Simple Church: returning to God's process for making disciples |location=Nashville, TN |publisher=B&H Publishing Group |date=2006 |isbn=9780805443905 |oclc=68810069 |url=https://archive.org/details/simplechurchretu00rain_1 }}\n*{{cite book |author1-last=Rainer |author1-first=Thom S. |author1-mask=3 |author2-last=Rainer |author2-first=Art |title=Raising Dad: What Fathers & Sons Learn from Each Other |location=Nashville, TN |publisher=B&H Publishing Group |date=2007 |isbn=978-0-805-44391-2 |url=https://archive.org/details/raisingdadwhatfa00artr }}\n*{{cite book |author1-last=Rainer |author1-first=Thom S. |author1-mask=3 |author2-last=Rainer |author2-first=Sam |title=Essential Church: reclaiming a generation of dropouts |location=Nashville, TN |publisher=B&H Publishing Group |date=2008 |isbn=978-0-805-44392-9 |oclc=209639048 }}\n*{{cite book |author1-last=Rainer |author1-first=Thom S. |author1-mask=3 |author2-last=Akin |author2-first=Daniel L. |author2-link=Daniel L. Akin |title=Vibrant Church: Becoming a Healthy Church in the 21st Century |location=Nashville, TN |publisher=B&H Publishing Group |date=2009 |isbn=978-1-415-86541-5 }}\n*{{cite book |author1-last=Rainer |author1-first=Thom S. |author1-mask=3 |author2-last=Rainer |author2-first=Art |title=Simple Life: time, relationships, money, God with Art Rainer |location=Nashville, TN |publisher=B&H Publishing Group |date=2009 |isbn=978-0-805-44886-3 |oclc=316018625 }}\n*{{cite book |author1-last=Rainer |author1-first=Thom S. |author1-mask=3 |author2-last=Stetzer |author2-first=Ed |title=Transformational Church: creating a new scorecard for congregations |location=Nashville, TN |publisher=B&H Publishing Group |date=2010 |isbn=978-1-433-66930-9 |oclc=645665198 }}\n*{{cite book |author1-last=Rainer |author1-first=Thom S. |author1-mask=3 |author2-last=Rainer |author2-first=Jess W. |title=The Millennials: connecting to America's largest generation |location=Nashville, TN |publisher=B&H Publishing Group |date=2011 |isbn=978-1-433-67003-9 |oclc=695042457 }}\n*{{cite book |author1-last=Rainer |author1-first=Thom S. |author1-mask=3 |title=I Am a Church Member: Discovering the Attitude that Makes the Difference |location=Nashville, TN |publisher=B&H Publishing Group |date=2013 |isbn=978-1-433-67973-5 |oclc=812571549 }}\n*{{cite book |author1-last=Rainer |author1-first=Thom S. |author1-mask=3 |title=Autopsy of a Deceased Church: 12 Ways to Keep Yours Alive |location=Nashville, TN |publisher=B&H Publishing Group |date=2014 |isbn=978-1-433-68392-3 |oclc=880741442 }}\n*{{cite book |author1-last=Rainer |author1-first=Thom S. |author1-mask=3 |title=I Will: Nine Traits of the Outwardly Focused Christian |location=Nashville, TN |publisher=B&H Publishing Group |date=2015 |isbn=978-1433687297 |oclc=894625832 }}\n*{{cite book |author1-last=Rainer |author1-first=Thom S. |author1-mask=3 |title=Who Moved My Pulpit?: Leading Change in the Church |location=Nashville, TN |publisher=B&H Publishing Group |date=2016 |isbn=978-1433643873 |oclc=929545252 }}\n\n===Articles and contributions===\n*{{cite journal |author1-last=Rainer |author1-first=Thom S. |author1-mask=3 |title=A Resurgence Not Yet Realized: Evangelistic Effectiveness in the Southern Baptist Convention Since 1979 |journal=[[Southern Baptist Journal of Theology]] |volume=9 |issue=1 |date=Spring 2005 |pages=54\u201369 |url=http://www.sbts.edu/resources/journal-of-theology/sbjt-91-spring-2005/a-resurgence-not-yet-realized-evangelistic-effectiveness-in-the/ |accessdate=June 17, 2016 }} - [http://www.sbts.edu/resources/files/2010/01/05sbjt_091_spr05-rainer.pdf PDF]\n*{{cite web|author1-last=Rainer |author1-first=Thom S. |author1-mask=3 |title=What Price Evangelism? |url=http://www.uu.edu/centers/rglee/fellows/spring04/rainer.htm |publisher=Union University |accessdate=June 17, 2016}}\n*{{cite web|author1-last=Rainer |author1-first=Thom S. |author1-mask=3 |title=Five Major Trends for Churches in America |url=http://www.christianpost.com/article/20100510/five-major-trends-for-churches-in-america/ |publisher=christianpost.com |accessdate=June 17, 2016}}\n*{{cite web|author1-last=Rainer |author1-first=Thom S. |author1-mask=3 |title=Seven Secrets of Healthy Churches |url=http://www.churchleaders.com/outreach-missions/outreach-missions-articles/139401-seven-secrets-of-healthy-churches.html |publisher=churchleaders.com |accessdate=June 17, 2016}}\n*{{cite web|author1-last=Rainer |author1-first=Thom S. |author1-mask=3 |title=What Millennials Want in Leaders |url=http://www.sbcbaptistpress.org/BPFirstPerson.asp?ID=34396 |publisher=sbcbaptistpress.org |accessdate=June 17, 2016 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120306034723/http://www.sbcbaptistpress.org/BPFirstPerson.asp?ID=34396 |archivedate=March 6, 2012 }}\n*{{cite web|author1-last=Rainer |author1-first=Thom S. |author1-mask=3 |title=Three Root Causes of Stalled Spiritual Transformation |url=http://www.sermoncentral.com/articlec.asp?article=Thom-Rainer-Three-Root-Causes-Stalled-Spiritual-Transformation&ac=true |publisher=sermoncentral.com |accessdate=June 17, 2016}}\n*{{cite web|author1-last=Rainer |author1-first=Thom S. |author1-mask=3 |title=Keys to Attracting the Unchurched |url=http://www.churchleaders.com/outreach-missions/outreach-missions-articles/139404-the-keys-to-attracting-the-unchurched.html |publisher=churchleaders.com |accessdate=June 17, 2016}}\n*{{cite book|author1-last=Rainer |author1-first=Thom S. |author1-mask=3  |chapter=By the Numbers: What SBC Demographics Tell Us about our Past, Present, and Future |editor1-last=Allen |editor1-first=Jason K. |editor1link=Jason K. Allen |title=The SBC and the 21st century |location=Nashville, TN |publisher=B&H Publishing Group |date=2016 |pages=21\u201332 |isbn=978-1433644399 |oclc=945352301 }}\n\n==See also==\n*[[List of Southern Baptist Convention affiliated people]]\n{{Portal bar|Biography|Christianity}}\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*{{official website|http://www.thomrainer.com/}}\n\n{{Southern Baptist Theological Seminary}}\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Rainer, Thom S.}}\n[[Category:1955 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:People from Union Springs, Alabama]]\n[[Category:American Christian theologians]]\n[[Category:American Christian writers]]\n[[Category:Southern Baptist ministers]]\n[[Category:Christian bloggers]]\n[[Category:University of Alabama alumni]]\n[[Category:Southern Baptist Theological Seminary alumni]]\n[[Category:Southern Baptist Theological Seminary faculty]]\n[[Category:Baptists from Alabama]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox academic\n| name        = Thom S. Rainer\n| image       =\n| image_size  = 66 KB\n| alt         = \n| caption     = \n| other_names = \n| birth_name  = \n| birth_date  = {{birth date and age|1955|07|16|mf=y}}\n| birth_place = [[Union Springs, Alabama]]\n| death_date  = \n| death_place = \n| nationality = American\n| citizenship =  \n| residence   = \n| occupation  = \n| known_for   = \n| title       = Former President and CEO, [[LifeWay Christian Resources]]\n| spouse      = Nellie Jo King\n| partner     = \n| children    = \n| discipline         = <!-- Major academic discipline - e.g. Physicist, Sociologist, New Testament scholar, Ancient Near Eastern Linguist -->\n| sub_discipline     = <!-- Academic discipline specialist area - e.g. Sub-atomic research, 20th Century Danish specialist, Pauline research, Arcadian and Ugaritic specialist -->\n| movement           = <!-- Should match the ideological movement or denomination (for religious), \"school\" of thought etc. (e.g. \"Anglican\", \"Postmodernist\", \"Socialist\" or \"Green\" etc. -->\n\n| education          = [[University of Alabama]]<br />[[Southern Baptist Theological Seminary]]\n| alma_mater         = <!-- will often consist of the linked name of the last-attended higher education institution. -->\n| thesis_title       = \n| thesis_url         = \n| thesis_year        = \n| school_tradition   = \n| doctoral_advisor   = \n| doctoral_students  = \n| notable_students   = <!--Only those with WP articles-->\n| main_interests     = \n| workplaces         = Southern Baptist Theological Seminary<!--full-time positions only, not student positions-->\n| notable_works      = \n| notable_ideas      = \n| influences         = <!--Must be referenced from a third party source-->\n| influenced         = <!--Must be referenced from a third party source-->\n| awards             = <!--Notable national level awards only-->\n| website            =\n| footnotes          =\n}}\n'''Thom S. Rainer''' (born July 16, 1955) is an [[United States|American]] writer, researcher, speaker, and former president and CEO of [[LifeWay Christian Resources]], an entity of the [[Southern Baptist Convention]]<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.sbc.net/aboutus/entities/lifeway.asp |publisher=Southern Baptist Convention |title=LifeWay Christian Resources |accessdate=2017-01-23}}</ref> in [[Nashville, Tennessee]]. He is the author of several best selling books, including ''I Am a Church Member'', named a [[CBA (Christian trade association)|CBA]] #1 Best Seller (2013\u20132014) and Monthly Best Seller (2013\u20132015).<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.christianretailing.com/index.php/newsletter/latest/26466-i-am-a-church-member-becomes-no-1-cba-best-seller |title='I Am a Church Member' becomes No. 1 CBA best-seller |publisher= Christian Retailing |date= |accessdate=2017-01-20}}</ref> It was also recognized as a Monthly Best Seller (2013\u20132015), a Gold Medallion Award winner (2015),<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ecpa.org/news/230065/ECPA-Presents-Diamond-Awards-to-three-Non-Fiction-titles-for-over-10-million-in-sales-17-other-titl.htm |title=ECPA Presents Diamond Awards to three Non-Fiction titles for over 10 million in sales; 17 other titles |publisher=ECPA |date= |accessdate=2017-01-20}}</ref> and a Platinum Book Award winner (2016)<ref>{{cite web|url=http://christianbookexpo.com/salesawards/ |title=Gold / Platinum / Diamond Book Awards Winners |publisher=Christian Book Expo |date= |accessdate=2017-01-20}}</ref> by the [[Evangelical Christian Publishers Association]], and recognized by Leadership Journal as Best of the Best in the Leaders Outer Life category (2013);<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.bhpublishinggroup.com/press-release/i-am-a-church-member-by-thom-rainer-impacts-1-million-people-in-its-first-two-years-of-release |title=I AM A CHURCH MEMBER BY THOM RAINER IMPACTS 1 MILLION PEOPLE IN ITS FIRST TWO YEARS OF RELEASE |publisher=B&H Publishing Group |date= |accessdate=2017-01-20}}</ref> ''Autopsy of a Deceased Church'', Christian Retailing's Best Book of the Year: Church and Culture (2015);<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.frontgatemedia.com/winners-announced-in-2015-christian-retailings-best-awards/ |title=Winners announced in 2015 Christian Retailing's Best awards |publisher=Front Gate Media |date=2015-07-06 |accessdate=2017-01-20}}</ref> and ''Simple Church'', the 2007 ''[[Christianity Today]]'' Book Award winner in the Church/Pastoral Leadership category.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.christianitytoday.com/ct/2007/june/8.36.html |title=2007 Christianity Today Book Awards |publisher=Christianity Today |date= |accessdate=2013-09-06}}</ref>\n\n==Biography==\nRainer was born in [[Union Springs, Alabama]] and is a 1977 graduate of the [[University of Alabama]], majoring in corporate finance with minors in [[statistics]] and [[economics]]. He began his career as a cash management officer (1977\u201380) at Trust Company of Georgia, now [[SunTrust]]. By age 25, Rainer became a fifth-generation banker and the youngest vice president<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.churchcentral.com/blog/Learn-the-Secret-of-Loving-Your-Work |title=Learn the Secret of Loving Your Work |publisher=ChurchCentral.com |date=2010-10-17 |accessdate=2013-09-06 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20101028180429/http://www.churchcentral.com/blog/Learn-the-Secret-of-Loving-Your-Work |archivedate=2010-10-28 }}</ref> for corporate lending of [[SouthTrust Bank]] in [[Anniston, Alabama]] (1980\u201383).\n\nRainer entered Christian vocational ministry in 1982 and earned his [[Master of Divinity]] and [[Doctor of Philosophy]] degrees from the [[Southern Baptist Theological Seminary]] in [[Louisville, Kentucky]]. He served as pastor of churches in Alabama, Florida, Kentucky and Indiana prior to joining the faculty of SBTS in 1994 as founding dean of the [[Billy Graham School of Missions, Evangelism and Church Growth]].<ref>[http://www.sbts.edu/bgs/faculty/thom-rainer/ ] {{webarchive |url=https://web.archive.org/web/20100527113648/http://www.sbts.edu/bgs/faculty/thom-rainer/ |date=May 27, 2010 }}</ref> Also while serving at SBTS, Rainer founded and served as president and CEO of the [[Rainer Group]].\n\nIn September 2005, Rainer was unanimously elected by the trustees of [[LifeWay Christian Resources]] to succeed [[James T. Draper]] as the ninth president of LifeWay,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.bpnews.net/bpnews.asp?id=21609 |title=Baptist Press -Thom Rainer gets unanimous vote as LifeWay president-elect - News with a Christian Perspective |publisher=Bpnews.net |accessdate=2013-09-06 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120403011143/http://www.bpnews.net/bpnews.asp?id=21609 |archivedate=2012-04-03 }}</ref> one of the world's largest Christian resource providers.<ref>{{cite book|url=https://books.google.com/?id=-fYDGf4U1psC&pg=PT774&lpg=PT774&dq=lifeway+world%27s+largest+christian+publisher#v=onepage&q=lifeway%20world's%20largest%20christian%20publisher&f=false |author1-last=Pope |author1-first=Alice |title=2010 Novel & Short Story Writer's Market |date=2010 |accessdate=2017-01-23|isbn=9781599635675 }}</ref> Shortly after assuming the presidency, Rainer established B&H Academic,<ref>{{cite web |url=https://blogs.thegospelcoalition.org/trevinwax/2013/12/13/know-your-southern-baptists-thom-rainer-2/ |title=KNOW YOUR SOUTHERN BAPTISTS: THOM RAINER |publisher=Kingdom People |date=2013-12-13 |accessdate=2017-01-23 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170202022926/https://blogs.thegospelcoalition.org/trevinwax/2013/12/13/know-your-southern-baptists-thom-rainer-2/ |archive-date=2017-02-02 |url-status=dead }}</ref> a branch of LifeWay's [[B&H Publishing Group]], to provide pastors, seminary professors and students with theologically conservative commentaries, academic monographs and other biblically-based resources.\n\n==Blog and podcast==\nRainer blogs at ThomRainer.com and hosts the highly rated Rainer on Leadership Podcast.<ref>[https://itunes.apple.com/us/podcast/rainer-on-leadership/id638894745?mt=2/ Rainer on Leadership]</ref> Rainer on Leadership, a twice weekly podcast which experienced 265 percent growth between 2014 and 2016, was started as a companion to Rainer's blog. It surpassed 100,000 monthly downloads in September 2016.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.bpnews.net/47740 |title=SBC DIGEST: Surgeon Rebekah Naylor honored; Rainer podcast surpasses 1M; Digby to lead MBC ethics arm; New FCA leader named |date=2016-10-18 |accessdate=2017-01-20}}</ref> His blog is listed at #6 on Redeeming God's list of Christian blogs.<ref>[https://redeeminggod.com/100-top-christian-blogs/ The 100 Top Christian Blogs]</ref>\n\n==LifeWay Research==\nNot long after becoming president of LifeWay, Rainer announced the formation of [[LifeWay Research]] for the purpose of assisting and equipping church leaders with insight and advice that will lead to greater levels of church health and effectiveness.<ref>[http://baptistpress.net/bpnews.asp?id=23234 ] {{webarchive |url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110723022927/http://baptistpress.net/bpnews.asp?id=23234 |date=July 23, 2011 }}</ref>\n\nLifeWay Research is frequently cited in religious and mainstream media, including [[The New York Times]],<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2016/10/17/us/donald-trump-evangelicals-republican-vote.html |title=Donald Trump Reveals Evangelical Rifts That Could Shape Politics for Years |work=New York Times |date=2016-10-17 |accessdate=2017-01-20}}</ref> [[USA Today]],<ref>{{cite web |url=http://content.usatoday.com/topics/topic/Religion+and+beliefs/Surveys/LifeWay+Research |archive-url=https://wayback.archive-it.org/all/20110915174345/http://content.usatoday.com/topics/topic/Religion+and+beliefs/Surveys/LifeWay+Research |url-status=dead |archive-date=2011-09-15 |title=LifeWay Research Topics Page - USATODAY.com |publisher=Content.usatoday.com |accessdate=2013-09-06 }}</ref> [[Washington Post]],<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/pb/news/acts-of-faith/wp/2016/10/07/donald-trumps-pastor-problem-40-percent-of-protestant-pastors-are-still-undecided/?outputType=accessibility&nid=menu_nav_accessibilityforscreenreader |title=Donald Trump's pastor problem: 40 percent of Protestant ministers are still undecided |publisher=Washington Post |date=2016-10-07 |accessdate=2017-01-20}}</ref> [[Christianity Today]],<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.christianitytoday.com/edstetzer/2016/november/lifeway-research-friends-and-family-matter-more-than-money.html |title=LifeWay Research: Friends and Family Matter More Than Money When It Comes to Giving Thanks |publisher=Christianity Today |date=2016-11-24 |accessdate=2017-01-20}}</ref> [[The Christian Post]],<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.christianpost.com/author/lifeway-research/ |title=Survey: Pastors Say Identifying With Denomination Will Become Less Vital |publisher=Christianpost.com |accessdate=25 February 2015}}</ref> and [[Baptist Press]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.bpnews.net/bpnews.asp?id=34409 |title=Baptist Press -BP 2010: YEAR IN REVIEW - LifeWay Research: Recession catches up to U.S. churches - News with a Christian Perspective |publisher=Bpnews.net |accessdate=2013-09-06 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120403011216/http://www.bpnews.net/bpnews.asp?id=34409 |archivedate=2012-04-03 }}</ref>\n\n==Great Commission resurgence==\nIn the 2005 Spring edition of the ''[[Southern Baptist Journal of Theology]]'', Rainer published a tribute and a review of the [[Southern Baptist Convention conservative resurgence]] after 25 years. The article entitled \"A Resurgence Not Yet Realized,\" noted that, though a theological turnaround had taken place in the Southern Baptist Convention, there was little indication that a resurgence of evangelism had taken place in the churches. In the article Rainer called for a \"great commission resurgence\", a phrase that would become the nomenclature for a renewed Great Commission emphasis in the SBC years later.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.pray4gcr.com/2010/05/thom-rainer-president-of-lifeway-doing-nothing-is-not-an-option-calls-for-gcr/ |accessdate=February 2, 2011 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110715111724/http://www.pray4gcr.com/2010/05/thom-rainer-president-of-lifeway-doing-nothing-is-not-an-option-calls-for-gcr/ |archivedate=July 15, 2011 }}</ref>\n\n==Awards and recognition==\nIn the spring of 2004, Rainer was invited to be a member of the Society of Fellows for the R. G. Lee Center for Christian Ministry at [[Union University]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.uu.edu/centers/rglee/fellows.cfm |title=Society of Fellows |publisher=Union University |accessdate=2017-01-23}}</ref>\n\nIn 2008, Rainer received the M. E. Dodd Denominational Service Award from [[Union University]].<ref name=\"uu.edu\">{{cite web|url=http://www.uu.edu/news/release.cfm?ID=1360 |title=Union presents Dodd Award to Rainer - News Release &#124; Union University |publisher=Uu.edu |date=2008-06-13 |accessdate=2013-09-06}}</ref> The Dodd Award is the highest denominational service award Union gives. It is named for the man who was a Union alumnus, served as president of the Southern Baptist Convention and who was the father of today's [[Cooperative Program]],<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.cpmissions.net/2003/what%20is%20cp.asp |title=Cooperative Program (CP) Missions |publisher=Cpmissions.net |date= |accessdate=2013-09-06}}</ref> the method by which Southern Baptists pool their resources to fund their mission efforts. The award is given annually to a leader within the SBC who displays excellence and leadership in Southern Baptist life, as well as friendship and commitment to Union University. Past recipients include [[James T. Draper|Jimmy Draper]] (2004), [[Adrian Rogers]] (2005), [[Morris Chapman]] (2006) and [[Frank Page (Southern Baptist)|Frank Page]] (2007).\n\nOn November 11, 2010, Rainer received the Donald A. McGavran award for outstanding leadership in church growth from the Great Commission Research Network.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://townhall.com/news/religion/2010/11/17/sbc_digest_rainer_receives_mcgavran_church_growth_award;_wright_speaks_at_southwestern;_ |title=SBC DIGEST: Rainer receives McGavran church growth award; Wright speaks at Southwestern;&nbsp;... - Baptist Press - Breaking News \u2013 Latest World, US, Science, Entertainment, Election, Technology News and Current Events |publisher=Townhall.com |date=2010-11-17 |accessdate=2013-09-06}}</ref> According to the GCRN president Bob Whitesel, Rainer's \"research and writings have been and continue to be key resources to those who care about church health and growth.\"<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.lifeway.com/article/170559/ |archive-url=https://archive.is/20130128122317/http://www.lifeway.com/article/170559/ |url-status=dead |archive-date=2013-01-28 |title=Thom Rainer named 2010 Donald A. McGavran award recipient |publisher=Lifeway.com |date=2010-11-16 |accessdate=2013-09-06 }}</ref>\n\nIn 2010, Rainer was inducted into the Carl F. H. Henry Society of Fellows at [[Union University]] and provided Union's graduation keynote address.<ref name=\"uu.edu\"/> Rainer was also appointed to serve as a trustee board member for Union by action of the Tennessee Baptist Convention.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.tnbaptist.org/page.asp?cat=aboutus&subcat=boards |title=Tennessee Baptist Convention |publisher=Tnbaptist.org |accessdate=2013-09-06 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131005072140/http://www.tnbaptist.org/page.asp?cat=aboutus&subcat=boards |archivedate=2013-10-05 }}</ref>\n\nThe [[Southern Baptist Theological Seminary]] awarded Rainer its Alumnus of the Year award in 2013<ref>{{cite web|url=http://news.sbts.edu/2013/06/13/at-2013-alumni-luncheon-southern-seminary-names-thom-rainer-alumnus-of-the-year/ |title=At 2013 alumni luncheon, Southern Seminary names Thom Rainer alumnus of the year |publisher=Southern News |date=2013-06-13 |accessdate=2017-01-20}}</ref> and the E.Y. Mullins Distinguished Denominational Service Award in 2014. In presenting the award, Southern's president, [[Albert Mohler]], recognized Rainer \"for his 'remarkable legacy of leadership' as pastor, scholar, teacher, and founding dean of the Billy Graham School, as well as for his role as author, speaker, and president of LifeWay Christian Resources of the Southern Baptist Convention.\"<ref>{{cite web|url=http://news.sbts.edu/2014/10/15/southern-seminary-trustees-celebrate-20th-anniversary-of-billy-graham-school/ |title=Southern Seminary trustees celebrate 20th anniversary of Billy Graham School |publisher=Southern News |date=2014-10-15 |accessdate=2017-01-20}}</ref>\n\n==Speaking and teaching==\nExamples of his speaking and teaching engagements include:\n*\"Evangelism and Church Growth in the Southern Baptist Convention,\" Baptist Identity II Conference<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.uu.edu/events/baptistidentity/ |title=Baptist Identity II: Convention, Cooperation and Controversy - Feb. 15-17, 2007 |publisher=Uu.edu |date= |accessdate=2013-09-06}}</ref>\n*\"The Church and Contemporary Culture,\" University of the Cumberlands.<ref>[http://gradweb.ucumberlands.edu/religion/macs/profiles/guest-speakers ] {{webarchive |url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110720082314/http://gradweb.ucumberlands.edu/religion/macs/profiles/guest-speakers |date=July 20, 2011 }}</ref>\n*Christian Executive Officers (CEO) Fellowship<ref>[http://www.ceofellowship.com/thom-rainer.html ]{{dead link|date=September 2013}}</ref>\n*The Commission on Evangelism<ref>{{cite web|url=http://nccumcevangelism.org/acw-advance-academy/ |accessdate=February 2, 2011 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20101023162744/http://nccumcevangelism.org/acw-advance-academy/ |archivedate=October 23, 2010 }}</ref>\n\n\nRainer holds the title of Distinguished Professor of Evangelism and Church Growth (2006) at The Southern Baptist Theological Seminary, and also lectures at [[Southeastern Baptist Theological Seminary]].\n\n==Works==\nRainer has written or co-written 27 books and more than 200 articles. His books and a selection of his articles include:\n\n=